<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

 <p>
 While visiting the "Site", you may be asked to register and/or provide information that personally identifies you ("Personal Information") for purposes of interacting with the Site. Such Personal Information may include, but is not limited to, your name and e-mail address. 
 </p>

<strong>Anonymous</strong>
<p>The whole point of Feedback Safe is to allow open anonymous communication. Your personal information or identity will at no time be divulged to the organization that you have engaged, or has engaged you in conversation. While "Leader" roles are identified in conversations, the user remains anonymous through all interactions with their organization. All server-side login information is handled and stored on FeedbackSafe.com and not with the target organization providing you with the protection of true anonymity.</p>

<strong>Cookies</strong>
<p>What are Cookies? A cookie is a small data text file that a web site sends to your browser, which is stored on your system. The Site can only access the information from a cookie sent by the Site. We cannot access cookies sent by other web sites or the information contained therein. Additionally, we cannot learn your e-mail address or any other information about you through the use of a cookie. The only way we would learn such information is if you specifically and voluntarily submit that information to us, for example, through a registration system, or by entering information.
</p>

<strong>Email</strong>
<p>As a user of this Site, your email was likely procured from a leader of an organization with which you are affiliated. Your email is not referenced during interaction with the target organization except for the purposes of sending receipts and notifications. At no time do organizations have access to what email is affiliated which what interaction. Email receipts and notifications may be turned off by opting out. </p>

<strong>Use of Personal Information</strong>
<p>We believe in protecting your privacy, and will not share Personal Information with third parties outside of the Company except as described in this Privacy Policy. We reserve the right to disclose Personal Information when needed to comply with the law or a legal process, cooperate with investigations of purported unlawful activities, to identify persons violating the law, or in connection with the sale of part or all of either of the Company or its respective affiliate's stock or assets.</p>

